section.div: A blog (engine) completely written in C# and Blazor. It aims to be a simple use and easy to extend platform. Blogposts are written in Markdown and are rendered to HTML. This gives all the flexibility needed to express yourself but also have an easy way of creating posts in the first place.

bUnit is a testing library for Blazor components that make tests look, feel, and runs like regular unit tests. bUnit makes it easy to render and control a component under test’s life-cycle, pass parameter and inject services into it, trigger event handlers, and verify the rendered markup from the component using a built-in semantic HTML comparer.
A collection of tips and tricks with smaller code snippets and explanation.
